oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Nashville Humane Association membership card
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Membership card for the Nashville Humane Association issued to Elise Croft. The card is signed by the executive secretary, Frances B. Hutchison.

In 1946, the Nashville Humane Association was formed to help with the welfare of Davidson County animals. The association was influenced by a former association from 1887 related to child labor conditions and the treatment of draft horses.
